Thanks to Agent LaBox who sent in the above clipping from a  recent issue of Portland's daily newspaper, <em>The Oregonian</em>. <a href="http://www.oregonlive.com/portland/oregonian/index.ssf?/base/portland_news/115490311761010.xml&amp;coll=7" target="_blank">The article</a> is about the excellent radical bookshop <a href="http://www.geocities.com/laughinghorsebooks/" target="_blank">Laughing Horse Books</a> (please note the linked-to page still has their old address, tsk tsk), and while the text doesn't mention CrimethInc., of course, the caption for the photo accompanying the print version of the article reads "Jessi Norris buys a book for her 14-year-old sister from Jack Piper at Laughing Horse Books . . ." The book, delightfully, is our very own <a href="/books/days.html"><em>Days of War Nights of Love</em></a>! (Click on photo for a larger image.) Thanks Jessi and Jack, and inquisitive 14-year-old sisters everywhere!]]></content_encoded>
